subsection.p:
The transpose A^T is an n\times m matrix having \rank(A^T) = \rank(A)= n. Since W^\perp = \nul(A^T), we have
\dim W^\perp = \dim\nul(A^T) = m - \rank(A^T) = m-n = m-\dim W\text{.}
This explains the following proposition.
